msgctxt "mn113:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 113 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 113 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn113:0.2"
msgid "Sappurisasutta "
msgstr "A Good Person "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn113:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn113:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn113:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn113:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn113:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn113:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

# NOTE: Here it seems "quality" seems better than "teaching" for dhamma. Nevertheless, I wonder whether teaching is not meant even here: the problem is glorifying oneself, which perhaps means in a Dhamma talk?
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn113:2.1"
msgid "“sappurisadhammañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asappurisadhammañca. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the qualities of a good person and the qualities of a bad person. "

msgctxt "mn113:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn113:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn113:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, pts-vp-pli3.38, sc2
msgctxt "mn113:3.1"
msgid "“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo? "
msgstr "“And what is a quality of a bad person? "

msgctxt "mn113:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, asappuriso uccākulā pabbajito hoti. "
msgstr "Take a bad person who has gone forth from an eminent family. "

msgctxt "mn113:3.3"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "They reflect: "

msgctxt "mn113:3.4"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi uccākulā pabbajito, ime panaññe bhikkhū na uccākulā pabbajitā’ti. "
msgstr "‘I have gone forth from an eminent family, unlike these other mendicants.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:3.5"
msgid "So tāya uccākulīnatāya attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that. "

#. VAR: Ayaṃ → ayampi (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn113:3.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr "This is a quality of a bad person. "

msgctxt "mn113:3.7"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "A good person reflects: "

msgctxt "mn113:3.8"
msgid "‘na kho uccākulīnatāya lobhadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, dosadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, mohadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti. "
msgstr "‘It’s not because of one’s eminent family that thoughts of greed, hate, or delusion come to an end. "

msgctxt "mn113:3.9"
msgid "No cepi uccākulā pabbajito hoti; "
msgstr "Even if someone has not gone forth from an eminent family, "

msgctxt "mn113:3.10"
msgid "so ca hoti dhammānudhammappaṭipanno sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī, so tattha pujjo, so tattha pāsaṃso’ti. "
msgstr "if they practice in line with the teaching, practice properly, and live in line with the teaching, they are worthy of honor and praise for that.’ "

# NOTE: antaram karitva is unusual here, normally it yields the expected sense of “hidden within”. Comm is no help.
msgctxt "mn113:3.11"
msgid "So paṭipadaṃyeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya uccākulīnatāya nevattānukkaṃseti na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "Keeping only the practice close to their heart, they don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of their eminent family. "

msgctxt "mn113:3.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (1) "
msgstr "This is a quality of a good person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4-6, sc3
msgctxt "mn113:4-6.1"
