msgctxt "mn113:15.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso rukkhamūliko hoti. "
msgstr "who stays at the root of a tree … "

msgctxt "mn113:15.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.3"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi rukkhamūliko, ime panaññe bhikkhū na rukkhamūlikā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.4"
msgid "So tena rukkhamūlikattena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.5"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.6"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.7"
msgid "‘na kho rukkhamūlikattena lobhadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, dosadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, mohadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.8"
msgid "No cepi rukkhamūliko hoti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.9"
msgid "so ca hoti dhammānudhammappaṭipanno sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī, so tattha pujjo, so tattha pāsaṃso’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.10"
msgid "So paṭipadaṃyeva antaraṃ karitvā tena rukkhamūlikattena nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:15.11"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (13) "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya16-20, sc13
msgctxt "mn113:16-20.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso sosāniko hoti … pe … "
msgstr "who stays in a charnel ground … "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.2"
msgid "abbhokāsiko hoti … "
msgstr "who stays in the open air … "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.3"
msgid "nesajjiko hoti … pe … "
msgstr "who never lies down … "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.4"
msgid "yathāsanthatiko hoti … pe … "
msgstr "who sleeps wherever they lay their mat... "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.5"
msgid "ekāsaniko hoti. "
msgstr "who eats in one sitting per day. "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.6"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "They reflect: "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.7"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi ekāsaniko, ime panaññe bhikkhū na ekāsanikā’ti. "
msgstr "‘I eat in one sitting per day, unlike these other mendicants.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.8"
msgid "So tena ekāsanikattena attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that. "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.9"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr "This too is a quality of a bad person. "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.10"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "A good person reflects: "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.11"
msgid "‘na kho ekāsanikattena lobhadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, dosadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti, mohadhammā vā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti. "
msgstr "‘It’s not because of eating in one sitting per day that thoughts of greed, hate, or delusion come to an end. "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.12"
msgid "No cepi ekāsaniko hoti; "
msgstr "Even if someone eats in more than one sitting per day, "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.13"
msgid "so ca hoti dhammānudhammappaṭipanno sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī, so tattha pujjo, so tattha pāsaṃso’ti. "
msgstr "if they practice in line with the teaching, practice properly, and live in line with the teaching, they are worthy of honor and praise for that.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.14"
msgid "So paṭipadaṃyeva antaraṃ karitvā tena ekāsanikattena nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "Keeping only the practice close to their heart, they don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of their eating in one sitting per day. "

msgctxt "mn113:16-20.15"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (14–18.) "
msgstr "This too is a quality of a good person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya21, pts-vp-pli3.43, sc14
msgctxt "mn113:21.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, take a bad person who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "mn113:21.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "They reflect: "

msgctxt "mn113:21.3"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi paṭhamajjhānasamāpattiyā lābhī, ime panaññe bhikkhū paṭhamajjhānasamāpattiyā na lābhino’ti. "
msgstr "‘I have attained the first absorption, unlike these other mendicants.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:21.4"
msgid "So tāya paṭhamajjhānasamāpattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that. "

msgctxt "mn113:21.5"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr "This too is a quality of a bad person. "

msgctxt "mn113:21.6"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "A good person reflects: "

msgctxt "mn113:21.7"
msgid "‘paṭhamajjhānasamāpattiyāpi kho atammayatā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr "‘The Buddha has spoken of not identifying even with the attainment of the first absorption. "

msgctxt "mn113:21.8"
msgid "Yena yena hi maññanti tato taṃ hoti aññathā’ti. "
msgstr "For whatever they think it is, it turns out to be something else.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:21.9"
msgid "So atammayataññeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya paṭhamajjhānasamāpattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "Keeping only non-identification close to their heart, they don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of their attainment of the first absorption. "

msgctxt "mn113:21.10"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (19) "
msgstr "This too is a quality of a good person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya22-24, sc15
msgctxt "mn113:22-24.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, take a bad person who, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, enters and remains in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.2"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.3"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.4"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "They reflect: "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.5"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi catutthajjhānasamāpattiyā lābhī, ime panaññe bhikkhū catutthajjhānasamāpattiyā na lābhino’ti. "
msgstr "‘I have attained the fourth absorption, unlike these other mendicants.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.6"
msgid "So tāya catutthajjhānasamāpattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that. "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.7"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr "This too is a quality of a bad person. "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.8"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "A good person reflects: "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.9"
msgid "‘catutthajjhānasamāpattiyāpi kho atammayatā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr "‘The Buddha has spoken of not identifying even with the attainment of the fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.10"
msgid "Yena yena hi maññanti tato taṃ hoti aññathā’ti. "
msgstr "For whatever they think it is, it turns out to be something else.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.11"
msgid "So atammayataññeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya catutthajjhānasamāpattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "Keeping only non-identification close to their heart, they don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of their attainment of the fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "mn113:22-24.12"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (20–22.) "
msgstr "This too is a quality of a good person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya25, sc16
msgctxt "mn113:25.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, take someone who, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space … "

msgctxt "mn113:25.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:25.3"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpattiyā lābhī, ime panaññe bhikkhū ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpattiyā na lābhino’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:25.4"
msgid "So tāya ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:25.5"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:25.6"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:25.7"
msgid "‘ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpattiyāpi kho atammayatā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:25.8"
msgid "Yena yena hi maññanti tato taṃ hoti aññathā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:25.9"
msgid "So atammayataññeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:25.10"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (23) "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya26, pts-vp-pli3.44, sc17
msgctxt "mn113:26.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "the dimension of infinite consciousness … "

msgctxt "mn113:26.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:26.3"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpattiyā lābhī, ime panaññe bhikkhū viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpattiyā na lābhino’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:26.4"
msgid "So tāya viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:26.5"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:26.6"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:26.7"
msgid "‘viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpattiyāpi kho atammayatā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:26.8"
msgid "Yena yena hi maññanti tato taṃ hoti aññathā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:26.9"
msgid "So atammayataññeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:26.10"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (24) "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya27, sc18
msgctxt "mn113:27.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "the dimension of nothingness … "

msgctxt "mn113:27.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:27.3"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpattiyā lābhī, ime panaññe bhikkhū ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpattiyā na lābhino’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:27.4"
msgid "So tāya ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:27.5"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:27.6"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:27.7"
msgid "‘ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpattiyāpi kho atammayatā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:27.8"
msgid "Yena yena hi maññanti tato taṃ hoti aññathā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:27.9"
msgid "So atammayataññeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn113:27.10"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (25) "
msgstr " "

#. REF: nya28, sc19
msgctxt "mn113:28.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. "

msgctxt "mn113:28.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "They reflect: "

msgctxt "mn113:28.3"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā lābhī, ime panaññe bhikkhū nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā na lābhino’ti. "
msgstr "‘I have attained the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, unlike these other mendicants.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:28.4"
msgid "So tāya nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "And they glorify themselves and put others down on account of that. "

msgctxt "mn113:28.5"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, asappurisadhammo. "
msgstr "This too is a quality of a bad person. "

msgctxt "mn113:28.6"
msgid "Sappuriso ca kho, bhikkhave, iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "A good person reflects: "

msgctxt "mn113:28.7"
msgid "‘nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyāpi kho atammayatā vuttā bhagavatā. "
msgstr "‘The Buddha has spoken of not identifying even with the attainment of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. "

msgctxt "mn113:28.8"
msgid "Yena yena hi maññanti tato taṃ hoti aññathā’ti. "
msgstr "For whatever they think it is, it turns out to be something else.’ "

msgctxt "mn113:28.9"
msgid "So atammayataññeva antaraṃ karitvā tāya nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti. "
msgstr "Keeping only non-identification close to their heart, they don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of their attainment of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. "

msgctxt "mn113:28.10"
msgid "Ayampi, bhikkhave, sappurisadhammo. (26) "
msgstr "This too is a quality of a good person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya29, pts-vp-pli3.45, sc20
#. VAR: cassa disvā āsavā → ekacce āsavā (mr)
msgctxt "mn113:29.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sappuriso sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati. Paññāya cassa disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā honti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, take a good person who, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements come to an end. "

#. VAR: Ayaṃ → ayaṃ kho (bj, s1-3, km) | ayampi (si) | ayaṃ pi (pts1)
msgctxt "mn113:29.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na kiñci maññati, na kuhiñci maññati, na kenaci maññatī”ti. (27) "
msgstr "This is a mendicant who does not identify with anything, does not identify regarding anything, does not identify through anything.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "mn113:29.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn113:29.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn113:29.5"
msgid "Sappurisasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

